<subSubSection id="C3163FFFFFD38E0BFF2DFEA4FBE8FEBB" box="[151,1028,331,358]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD38E0BFF2DFEA4FBE8FEBB" blockId="4.[151,1436,331,717]" box="[151,1028,331,358]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFF2DFEA4FEF2FEB8" bold="true" box="[151,286,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Etymology.</emphasis>
The 'polycomus' refers to the strongly pubescent body of the new.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3163FFFFFD38E0BFF7DFE80FDB0FE0C" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD38E0BFF7DFE80FDB0FE0C" blockId="4.[151,1436,331,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFF7DFE80FEAEFE54" bold="true" box="[199,322,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus has a distinct epiphallus (
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD38E0BFD5BFE80FCB6FE54" box="[737,858,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[166,1391,739,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-222@4.[160,1427,739,1934]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genitalia. A–C. Trigonidium rubrumoculus sp. nov. D–F. Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. A, D. Dorsal view. B, E. Lateral view. C, F. Ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417207/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Fig. 4D–F</figureCitation>
). Epiphallic median lobe scimitar-like, and the apex curved outward. Epiphallic lateral lobe nearly shaped as a rectangular. The sclerotized portion of ectoparamere sickle-like, tapering and apically obtuse.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3163FFFFFD38E0BFF7DFE34FC61FD10" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD38E0BFF7DFE34FC61FD10" blockId="4.[151,1436,331,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFF7DFE34FED7FE28" bold="true" box="[199,315,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new genus is similar in appearance to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD38E0BFC92FE34FAE8FE28" authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1893" box="[808,1284,475,502]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFC92FE34FC49FE28" box="[808,933,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D1185FFD38E0BFC16FE33FAE8FE28" author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, K." box="[940,1284,475,502]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" pagination="5 - 230" refId="ref2341" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, K. (1893) Revision du systeme des orthopteres et description des especes rapportees par M. Leonardo Fea de Birmanie. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, Series 2, 13, 5 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5121" type="journal article" year="1893">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but varies in male genitalia traits. The epiphallic lateral lobe of this new genus is slightly rectangular in shape and armed with a truncated tip, and the ectoparamere is sickle-shaped. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD38E0BFD5DFDCCFC88FDE0" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1893" box="[743,868,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFD5DFDCCFC88FDE0" box="[743,868,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the other hand, has a rod-like epiphallic lateral lobe and a truncated ectoparamere apex (Asian species, e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD38E0BFCE4FDA8FAFDFDBC" authority="He et al. 2010" authorityName="He" authorityYear="2010" box="[862,1297,583,610]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFCE4FDA8FBB0FDBC" box="[862,1116,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus bispinosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D1185FFD38E0BFBDCFDA7FAFDFDBC" author="He, Z. Q. &amp; Li, K. &amp; Fang, Y. &amp; Liu, X. W." box="[1126,1297,583,610]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" pagination="55 - 62" refId="ref2641" refString="He, Z. Q., Li, K., Fang, Y. &amp; Liu, X. W. (2010) A taxonomic study of the genus Amusurgus Brunner von Wanttenwyl from China (Orthoptera, Gryllidae, Trigonidiinae). Zootaxa, 2423 (1), 55 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2423.1.4" type="journal article" year="2010">
He 
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFB2BFDA7FB21FDBC" box="[1169,1229,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD38E0BFAA5FDA8FDDEFD58" authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFAA5FDA8FF36FD58" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus fulvus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D1185FFD38E0BFF5AFD83FDDEFD58" author="Brunner von Wattenwyl, K." box="[224,562,619,646]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" pagination="5 - 230" refId="ref2341" refString="Brunner von Wattenwyl, K. (1893) Revision du systeme des orthopteres et description des especes rapportees par M. Leonardo Fea de Birmanie. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, Series 2, 13, 5 - 230. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 5121" type="journal article" year="1893">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD38E0BFDD1FD84FC28FD58" authority="Tan, 2022" authorityName="Tan" authorityYear="2022" box="[619,964,619,646]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulus">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFDD1FD84FCA2FD58" box="[619,846,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus caerulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D1185FFD38E0BFCEEFD83FC28FD58" author="Tan, M. K." box="[852,964,619,646]" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" pagination="453 - 463" refId="ref2748" refString="Tan, M. K. (2022) A new aboreal species of sword-tailed cricket (Orthoptera: Trigonidiidae: Trigonidiinae) from the mangrove in Singapore. Zootaxa, 5092 (4), 453 - 463. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5092.4.4" type="journal article" year="2022">Tan, 2022</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) or a finger-like epiphallic lateral lobe and median lobe (Australian species, e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD38E0BFDF1FD60FBA3FD74" authority="Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983" authorityName="Otte &amp; Alexander" authorityYear="1983" box="[587,1103,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kanyakis">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFDF1FD60FCDEFD74" box="[587,818,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus kanyakis</emphasis>
Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD38E0BFBE6FD60FEB8FD10" authority="Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983" authorityName="Otte &amp; Alexander" authorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minmirri">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFBE6FD60FAA9FD74" box="[1116,1349,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus minmirri</emphasis>
Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C17F7FFD38E0BFE34FD5CFC6CFD10" authority="Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983" authorityName="Otte &amp; Alexander" authorityYear="1983" box="[398,896,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Trigonidiidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nilarius">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD38E0BFE34FD5CFD85FD10" box="[398,617,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="589">Amusurgus nilarius</emphasis>
Otte &amp; Alexander, 1983
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
